From: Thomas Petazzoni <thomas.petazzoni@free-electrons.com>
Date: Wed, 23 Dec 2015 11:50:11 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 20/31] Add an option to disable NIS

NIS is not necessarily available in uClibc, so we need an option to
not compile support for it.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Petazzoni <thomas.petazzoni@free-electrons.com>
---
 configure.ac | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/configure.ac b/configure.ac
index f5a758b..541f150 100644
--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -3139,6 +3139,14 @@ AC_ARG_ENABLE(codecs-cjk,
 	fi])
 AC_MSG_RESULT($DISABLED_EXTENSIONS)
 
+AC_MSG_CHECKING(for --disable-nis)
+AC_ARG_ENABLE(nis,
+	AS_HELP_STRING([--disable-nis], [disable NIS]),
+	[ if test "$enableval" = "no"; then
+    	     DISABLED_EXTENSIONS="${DISABLED_EXTENSIONS} nis"
+  	  fi])
+AC_MSG_RESULT($DISABLED_EXTENSIONS)
+
 AC_SUBST(TK)
 AC_MSG_CHECKING(for --disable-tk)
 AC_ARG_ENABLE(tk,
